    <img id="main-image" src="https://cdn.worldvectorlogo.com/logos/react-2.svg" alt="" width="50%" height="auto">
</div>

<div class="text-center p-4" style="font-family: Numans;">
    <h2>What Is Learn To React?</h2>
</div>

<div class="text-center">
    <p>A collection of <strong>free</strong> resources that our team has gathered to help you get the most out of the React curriculum from <a href="https://www.learnhowtoprogram.com">learnhowtoprogram.com</a></p>
</div>

<div class="text-center p-4" style="font-family: Numans;">
    <h2>What We'll Cover:</h2>
</div>

<div class="accordion accordion-parted" id="accordionExample3">
    <div class="card mb-3 border border-dark">
        <div class="card-header accbn632-hover accbn20 btn btn-outline-secondary border-0 rounded-top "id="headingIntro" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseIntro" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseIntro">
        <h4 class="mb-0">
            <strong>Introduction To React</strong>
        </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseIntro" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingIntro" data-parent="#accordionExample3">
        <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="text-center">
            <p>Learn about what React is and why it's so powerful. From JSX to the Virtual Dom, this is where we'll give you the tools you need to get started on your own React projects.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-3 border border-dark">
        <div class="card-header accbn632-hover accbn20 btn btn-outline-secondary border-0 rounded-top"id="headingFundamentalOne" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFundamentalOne" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFundamentalOne">
        <h4 class="mb-0">
            <strong>Fundamentals (Part 1)</strong>
        </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseFundamentalOne" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFundamentalOne" data-parent="#accordionExample3">
        <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="text-center">
            <p>Learn how to plan & build a static site, props, propTypes & loops, debugging with React Developer Tools, and different ways to style in React.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-3 border border-dark">
        <div class="card-header accbn632-hover accbn20 btn btn-outline-secondary border-0 rounded-top" id="headingFundamentalTwo" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFundamentalTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFundamentalTwo">
        <h4 class="mb-0">
            <strong>Fundamentals (Part 2)</strong>
        </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseFundamentalTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFundamentalTwo" data-parent="#accordionExample3">
        <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="text-center">
            <p>More fundamental concepts before going on to the advance stuff. 5 separate lessons on State in React, then we go into UUID and Re-using components.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-3 border border-dark">
        <div class="card-header accbn632-hover accbn20 btn btn-outline-secondary border-0 rounded-top"id="headingRedux" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseRedux" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseRedux">
        <h4 class="mb-0">
            <strong>Redux</strong>
        </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseRedux" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingRedux" data-parent="#accordionExample3">
        <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="text-center">
            <p>Learn about state management and Redux fundamental principles that help in maintaining consistency throughout your application, which makes debugging and testing easier!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-3 border border-dark">
        <div class="card-header accbn632-hover accbn20 btn btn-outline-secondary border-0 rounded-top"id="headingNoSQL" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseNoSQL" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseNoSQL">
        <h4 class="mb-0">
            <strong>NoSQL & Firebase</strong>
        </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseNoSQL" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingNoSQL" data-parent="#accordionExample3">
        <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="text-center">
            <p>Learn about the differences between SQL & NoSQL databases, and how to use the BaaS services available through Firebase and Firestore. We'll also cover how to effectively implement React hooks, React Router, and how to style your projects with Styled-Components!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-3 border border-dark">
        <div class="card-header accbn632-hover accbn20 btn btn-outline-secondary border-0 rounded-top"id="headingApi" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseApi" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseApi">
        <h4 class="mb-0">
            <strong>API's</strong>
        </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseApi" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingApi" data-parent="#accordionExample3">
        <div class="card-body text-center">
            <div class="text-center">
            <p>In this course section, we'll explore making API calls from a React application, using custom middleware to use async actions with Redux & combining a React front end with a .NET or Rails API</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


